text: Blaignan-Prignac is a commune in the Gironde department in Nouvelle-Aquitaine in southwestern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Blaignan (the seat) and Prignac-en-Médoc.Arrêté préfectoral 1 October 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Gironde department ==References== Category:Communes of Gironde
title: Blaignan-Prignac
